00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:29,059
There's a problem.

460
00:29:29,059 --> 00:29:30,500
See, God knows.

461
00:29:31,500 --> 00:29:34,619
Somebody made this comment to me years ago.

462
00:29:34,619 --> 00:29:37,219
In fact, John Feudo made the comment to me.

463
00:29:37,219 --> 00:29:40,219
He went over to Cape Verde for a missions trip,

464
00:29:40,219 --> 00:29:42,459
and he made this comment when he came back.

465
00:29:42,459 --> 00:29:45,859
He said, you know, the difference between them and America,

466
00:29:45,859 --> 00:29:48,099
Cape Verde, the people there in America,

467
00:29:48,099 --> 00:29:52,059
is that in America, we have money to cover up our problems.

468
00:29:53,979 --> 00:29:56,099
And he said, there, they don't have any money,

469
00:29:56,099 --> 00:29:57,979
and it's just right in your face,

470
00:29:57,979 --> 00:30:00,579
all of the sin and the wickedness and the turmoil.

471
00:30:00,579 --> 00:30:02,019
on the problems.

472
00:30:02,019 --> 00:30:04,259
Some of you have visited countries like that.

473
00:30:05,459 --> 00:30:08,459
But you know, the reality is that sometimes what we do,

474
00:30:09,379 --> 00:30:13,379
if we're not careful, we know how to put on the suit,

475
00:30:15,619 --> 00:30:17,939
we know how to put on the smile,

476
00:30:17,939 --> 00:30:20,979
we know how to come into the, and do our duty,

477
00:30:20,979 --> 00:30:23,659
do our work, do whatever it is,

478
00:30:23,659 --> 00:30:28,659
but oh, there's conflict, there's friction,

479
00:30:28,979 --> 00:30:30,219
there's sin.

480
00:30:31,259 --> 00:30:33,779
See, the Bible talks about sin being in the camp,

481
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:36,339
and it affects the whole.

482
00:30:37,259 --> 00:30:40,999
Can I remind you this evening, I remind myself tonight,

483
00:30:40,999 --> 00:30:43,859
that God is never okay with sin.

484
00:30:43,859 --> 00:30:45,419
Our God is a holy God.

485
00:30:47,299 --> 00:30:49,819
And our God, who is a holy God,

486
00:30:49,819 --> 00:30:53,459
said that we are to walk in holiness,

487
00:30:53,459 --> 00:30:56,299
that we are to be holy as he is holy.

488
00:30:57,299 --> 00:30:59,339
And there are times in which we look at the scriptures

489
00:30:59,339 --> 00:31:02,519
and the scriptures hit us right in the face.

490
00:31:03,619 --> 00:31:05,339
And we know there's something we gotta deal with.

491
00:31:05,339 --> 00:31:07,739
The Holy Spirit might prick our heart,

492
00:31:07,739 --> 00:31:11,979
and we just say no, and we quench,

493
00:31:11,979 --> 00:31:14,899
and we grieve the Holy Spirit.

494
00:31:14,899 --> 00:31:17,619
We don't deal with the things that we need to deal with

495
00:31:17,619 --> 00:31:20,539
because we think God's just gonna be okay with it.

496
00:31:21,699 --> 00:31:22,619
But what starts happening

497
00:31:22,619 --> 00:31:25,419
is we start losing the blessing of God.

498
00:31:25,419 --> 00:31:27,939
I don't wanna live without the blessing of God.

499
00:31:28,939 --> 00:31:33,459
I don't wanna just go through life getting by.

500
00:31:33,459 --> 00:31:35,339
I want God's favor.

501
00:31:35,339 --> 00:31:37,699
I want God's blessing.

502
00:31:37,699 --> 00:31:40,179
I truly desire this evening for myself

503
00:31:40,179 --> 00:31:41,559
and for our church family

504
00:31:41,559 --> 00:31:45,299
that there would be nothing between my soul and my Savior.

505
00:31:45,299 --> 00:31:48,979
That we could say, as Paul says in Acts 24 and verse 16,

506
00:31:48,979 --> 00:31:52,379
that I hereby exercise myself to do what?

507
00:31:52,379 --> 00:31:55,899
To have always a conscience void of offense

508
00:31:55,899 --> 00:32:00,239
toward God and toward men.

509
00:32:01,179 --> 00:32:02,299
Sometimes we deceive ourselves.

510
00:32:02,299 --> 00:32:04,579
Oh, I'm right with God, but you're wrong with your family.

511
00:32:04,579 --> 00:32:05,899
You're wrong with your friends.

512
00:32:05,899 --> 00:32:07,499
You're wrong with your church family.

513
00:32:07,499 --> 00:32:09,699
No, no, hold on a minute.

514
00:32:09,699 --> 00:32:13,179
Paul says, I'm exercising to be right with God,

515
00:32:13,179 --> 00:32:16,739
but also to be right with others.

516
00:32:16,739 --> 00:32:20,979
Conflict, it's terrible, it's terrible.

517
00:32:22,539 --> 00:32:24,539
I preached a message not long ago on a Sunday morning

518
00:32:24,539 --> 00:32:27,919
of how to handle strained relationships.

519
00:32:27,919 --> 00:32:28,939
What did I say in that message?

520
00:32:28,939 --> 00:32:31,539
Listen, we all deal with it in life at some point,

521
00:32:32,659 --> 00:32:34,019
but how do we deal with it?

522
00:32:35,059 --> 00:32:36,479
And sometimes we say, well, we ignore it.

523
00:32:36,479 --> 00:32:38,579
That's for somebody else.

524
00:32:38,579 --> 00:32:40,539
No, Lord, that's for me

525
00:32:40,539 --> 00:32:43,859
because I want your blessing in my life.

526
00:32:45,419 --> 00:32:48,539
Listen, I know the indictment against me

527
00:32:48,539 --> 00:32:51,439
and against us tonight would be different

528
00:32:51,439 --> 00:32:55,719
than the indictment against Israel in Hosea 10,

529
00:32:55,719 --> 00:32:58,159
but I just wonder tonight, what would it be?

530
00:32:58,159 --> 00:33:00,079
What would God say about your life?

531
00:33:00,079 --> 00:33:03,959
You know how many people in the last two years,

532
00:33:03,959 --> 00:33:05,959
we only got 10 minutes and I gotta get through the message,

533
00:33:05,959 --> 00:33:07,519
but in the last two years,

534
00:33:09,279 --> 00:33:14,079
I've had person after person after person

535
00:33:15,999 --> 00:33:19,679
call me or sit in my office

536
00:33:19,679 --> 00:33:21,919
about this one sin of pornography.

537
00:33:23,119 --> 00:33:26,199
Can I tell you, it's wicked, it's ungodly.

538
00:33:26,199 --> 00:33:28,959
God is never okay with it.

539
00:33:28,959 --> 00:33:30,439
If you look at the statistics,

540
00:33:30,439 --> 00:33:33,719
it's not just men that are affected with pornography.

541
00:33:33,719 --> 00:33:36,119
You look at the statistics, it's awful.

542
00:33:36,119 --> 00:33:39,239
And I don't speak about it often from this pulpit,

543
00:33:39,239 --> 00:33:42,739
but the reality is that it's killing our churches.

544
00:33:42,739 --> 00:33:45,879
It is absolutely destroying our homes.

545
00:33:46,879 --> 00:33:50,439
It's awful, wicked, vile.

546
00:33:50,439 --> 00:33:52,719
There was a stretch last year in about six months

547
00:33:52,719 --> 00:33:55,639
that I dealt with people that were in their teen years,

548
00:33:55,639 --> 00:33:59,859
their 20s, their 30s, their 40s, their 50s, and their 60s,

549
00:34:00,719 --> 00:34:02,699
all with the same problem.

550
00:34:02,699 --> 00:34:05,319
They weren't all from our church.

551
00:34:05,319 --> 00:34:07,279
There have been people that have come to our church,

552
00:34:07,279 --> 00:34:08,839
they visit our church one time

553
00:34:08,839 --> 00:34:10,319
and they say, I gotta meet with you,

554
00:34:10,319 --> 00:34:12,179
and I find out that I meet with them

555
00:34:12,179 --> 00:34:14,159
and their life is absolutely destroyed

556
00:34:14,159 --> 00:34:16,199
because of one thing, pornography.

557
00:34:17,599 --> 00:34:19,679
And they say, I just need help.

558
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:20,519
But you know what?

559
00:34:20,519 --> 00:34:21,339
They don't come back to church,

560
00:34:21,339 --> 00:34:23,479
so they don't really get the help that they need.

561
00:34:23,479 --> 00:34:26,319
They want a quick fix for their problem.

562
00:34:26,319 --> 00:34:28,159
There's no quick fix.

563
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:29,839
But I'm telling you this evening

564
00:34:29,839 --> 00:34:32,279
that God knows all that stuff.

565
00:34:32,279 --> 00:34:34,919
God sees all that stuff.

566
00:34:34,919 --> 00:34:35,939
What would the indictment be

567
00:34:35,939 --> 00:34:38,919
on the 21st century church tonight?

568
00:34:38,919 --> 00:34:42,319
We see what it is of Israel, but what is it of us?

569
00:34:42,319 --> 00:34:43,319
We have conflict.

570
00:34:43,319 --> 00:34:45,299
Oh, personal conflict isn't that big of a deal.

571
00:34:45,299 --> 00:34:46,519
It is a big deal.

572
00:34:47,519 --> 00:34:48,399
It's a big deal.

573
00:34:49,999 --> 00:34:51,799
And sometimes we think, well, it's not,

574
00:34:51,799 --> 00:34:54,359
my sin isn't that big.

575
00:34:54,359 --> 00:34:58,799
You messed up because the Bible says if I confess my sin,

576
00:34:58,799 --> 00:35:00,519
if I say the same thing about it,

577
00:35:00,519 --> 00:35:05,199
I agree with God that it's wickedness.

578
00:35:05,199 --> 00:35:07,039
Joseph said it this way.

579
00:35:07,039 --> 00:35:12,039
How can I do this great wickedness and sin against God?

580
00:35:13,279 --> 00:35:15,239
You know, it's a great study if you do a contrast

581
00:35:15,239 --> 00:35:18,039
between the life of Joseph and David

582
00:35:18,039 --> 00:35:22,079
with regard to the temptation that each of them faced.

583
00:35:22,079 --> 00:35:25,439
Joseph put on his running shoes,

584
00:35:25,439 --> 00:35:27,759
lost his coat, but retained his character.

585
00:35:28,719 --> 00:35:31,919
David, who is that woman?

586
00:35:31,919 --> 00:35:33,279
Bring her to me.

587
00:35:33,279 --> 00:35:35,199
Oh, well, she's the wife of Uriah.

588
00:35:36,279 --> 00:35:41,279
Hello, warning sign, bring her to me.

589
00:35:41,279 --> 00:35:46,279
He goes on to not only commit adultery, but murder.

590
00:35:49,599 --> 00:35:52,199
Listen, God is holy.

591
00:35:53,679 --> 00:35:56,679
I don't know what the indictment would be in your life,

592
00:35:56,679 --> 00:35:58,759
but I want to examine my life to know what is God?

593
00:35:58,759 --> 00:36:00,719
Does God have a controversy with me?

594
00:36:02,119 --> 00:36:03,479
Is there something in my life,

595
00:36:03,479 --> 00:36:04,439
is there something in your life

596
00:36:04,439 --> 00:36:07,119
that's withholding the blessing of God?

597
00:36:08,039 --> 00:36:11,959
It reveals to me this evening that God knows.

598
00:36:11,959 --> 00:36:13,319
Notice not only the indictment,

599
00:36:13,319 --> 00:36:15,079
but very quickly this evening,

600
00:36:16,439 --> 00:36:20,359
back in our text in Hosea 10, we note the instruction.

601
00:36:20,359 --> 00:36:22,639
We read it already in verse number 12.

602
00:36:23,559 --> 00:36:24,959
God knew their condition.

603
00:36:24,959 --> 00:36:28,719
He knew that judgment was on the horizon.

604
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:32,519
However, we find that God in his grace and his mercy,

605
00:36:32,519 --> 00:36:35,479
he instructs the people of Israel.

606
00:36:35,679 --> 00:36:37,919
Notice as we begin looking at verse 12,

607
00:36:37,919 --> 00:36:39,959
and we read it by way of introduction,

608
00:36:39,959 --> 00:36:43,079
that that principle, that law of sowing and reaping

609
00:36:43,079 --> 00:36:45,279
is mentioned to us to begin the verse,

610
00:36:45,279 --> 00:36:49,959
sow to yourselves in righteousness, reap in mercy.

611
00:36:49,959 --> 00:36:52,279
Then he tells them this, notice this phrase,

612
00:36:52,279 --> 00:36:54,759
it's used as the title of the message this evening,

613
00:36:54,759 --> 00:36:58,439
break up your fallow ground.

614
00:36:58,439 --> 00:37:03,279
The idea of this phrase in Hosea 10 in verse number 12

615
00:37:03,319 --> 00:37:06,119
is that they needed to prepare their hearts.

616
00:37:06,119 --> 00:37:07,679
See, their hearts were hard.

617
00:37:09,039 --> 00:37:11,239
Remember, their heart, according to verse number two,

618
00:37:11,239 --> 00:37:12,679
was divided.

619
00:37:13,599 --> 00:37:16,199
And God says, break up your fallow ground.

620
00:37:16,199 --> 00:37:19,999
And I love, and God is all wise,

621
00:37:20,839 --> 00:37:24,199
but he uses for us here in Hosea 10 in verse number 12,

622
00:37:24,199 --> 00:37:25,999
a relatable analogy.

623
00:37:27,239 --> 00:37:29,359
See, the natural process

624
00:37:30,359 --> 00:37:34,559
with regard to having a garden

625
00:37:34,559 --> 00:37:38,879
or having a farm and all acres and acres,

626
00:37:38,879 --> 00:37:41,599
however the size of it might be,

627
00:37:41,599 --> 00:37:45,599
the natural process is that the soil needs attention

628
00:37:45,599 --> 00:37:46,999
before the seed is put in.

629
00:37:48,239 --> 00:37:50,559
You know, the soil has a tendency to get hard.

630
00:37:51,479 --> 00:37:53,239
That's what happens.

631
00:37:53,239 --> 00:37:54,479
Weeds grow.

632
00:37:54,479 --> 00:37:56,439
How many of you got a garden this year?

633
00:37:57,439 --> 00:38:00,439
How many of you have a garden and you pulled weeds at all?

634
00:38:01,359 --> 00:38:04,159
How many of you noticed that after you pulled the weeds,

635
00:38:04,159 --> 00:38:05,999
a few days later, it seems like you go out

636
00:38:05,999 --> 00:38:08,479
and you're like, what in the world is going on?

637
00:38:09,439 --> 00:38:11,119
I told Holly, we made an agreement.

638
00:38:11,119 --> 00:38:12,719
I would help get the garden put in

639
00:38:12,719 --> 00:38:14,999
and she would weed the garden.

640
00:38:14,999 --> 00:38:16,119
That worked well.

641
00:38:17,719 --> 00:38:20,679
And the reality is that the weeds, they just keep coming.

642
00:38:21,559 --> 00:38:23,239
You know, the Bible says that Solomon

643
00:38:23,239 --> 00:38:24,199
in the book of Proverbs,

644
00:38:24,199 --> 00:38:25,959
that he went by a field that was overgrown.

645
00:38:26,479 --> 00:38:27,959
And he learned a lesson from it.

646
00:38:27,959 --> 00:38:30,759
You know, we can learn lessons from the fields.

647
00:38:30,759 --> 00:38:35,759
You can learn lessons from just doing simple earthly tasks.

648
00:38:36,839 --> 00:38:39,839
And if you go, we're nearing the end.

649
00:38:39,839 --> 00:38:41,119
September 1st is tomorrow.

650
00:38:41,119 --> 00:38:45,759
We're nearing the end of our typical gardening season

651
00:38:45,759 --> 00:38:47,879
here in our region.

652
00:38:47,879 --> 00:38:51,519
And before long, we'll take the last of our fruits

653
00:38:51,519 --> 00:38:54,879
from our gardens and we will enjoy them.

654
00:38:54,879 --> 00:38:56,919
And then all winter long,

655
00:38:56,919 --> 00:38:59,759
you know what's gonna happen to your soil and to my soil?

656
00:39:00,759 --> 00:39:01,759
It's gonna get hard.

657
00:39:02,919 --> 00:39:04,399
It's gonna get hard.

658
00:39:04,399 --> 00:39:06,879
And you know what's gonna happen in the spring

659
00:39:06,879 --> 00:39:09,839
is after the hard winter, and it doesn't really matter,

660
00:39:09,839 --> 00:39:11,159
even if we have a mild winter,

661
00:39:11,159 --> 00:39:13,359
it still happens that the soil gets hard.

662
00:39:13,359 --> 00:39:15,279
And we go out there in the spring

663
00:39:15,279 --> 00:39:16,399
and all of a sudden in the spring,

664
00:39:16,399 --> 00:39:18,199
we just go out there, we take a pack of seeds

665
00:39:18,199 --> 00:39:19,679
and we just throw them down and that's it.

666
00:39:19,679 --> 00:39:20,559
That's all we do.

667
00:39:21,759 --> 00:39:22,759
What's gonna happen?

668
00:39:23,639 --> 00:39:24,479
Probably nothing.

669
00:39:28,519 --> 00:39:31,759
You're not gonna go out there and expect to have fruit,

670
00:39:31,759 --> 00:39:33,439
to have those vegetables, to have that.

671
00:39:33,439 --> 00:39:34,479
No, why?

672
00:39:34,479 --> 00:39:36,959
Because you gotta do some stuff to the soil.

673
00:39:36,959 --> 00:39:38,439
You gotta prepare the soil.

674
00:39:38,439 --> 00:39:42,479
Our soil, at least here, we got a high amount of clay

675
00:39:43,719 --> 00:39:44,959
in our soil.

676
00:39:44,959 --> 00:39:46,639
So Dean, the master gardener,

677
00:39:46,639 --> 00:39:48,159
when we first started our garden, he said,

678
00:39:48,159 --> 00:39:51,279
pastor, you gotta put some peat moss in that thing.

679
00:39:51,519 --> 00:39:52,359
Why?

680
00:39:52,359 --> 00:39:54,839
Because it'll help keep it from clumping up so much

681
00:39:54,839 --> 00:39:58,799
and the roots can take and grow deep and get the water.

682
00:39:58,799 --> 00:40:00,599
And so, listen, in the spring.

683
00:40:00,599 --> 00:40:09,039
you know what we do? We work on that thing. We work on it. Why? Because we want to get

684
00:40:09,039 --> 00:40:16,099
a harvest. And God uses this relatable analogy that these people could understand even more

685
00:40:16,099 --> 00:40:21,119
than we can. I'm not a farmer, don't claim to be one. I think, we talk about being in

686
00:40:21,119 --> 00:40:25,359
Idaho, man, those people live right off the land, Montana. I'd probably die. I'm just

687
00:40:25,359 --> 00:40:28,959
being honest. I mean, I don't know how to do that stuff. They say, oh man, just go out

688
00:40:28,959 --> 00:40:32,599
and kill this animal and kill that animal. I wouldn't know what to do with it, man. I

689
00:40:32,599 --> 00:40:36,319
get my meat pre-prepared at Walmart, praise the Lord. Somebody else does all that for

690
00:40:36,319 --> 00:40:44,419
me. But you understand, like, they would understand this. Break up your fallow ground. Prepare

691
00:40:44,419 --> 00:40:51,119
your heart. And what are we doing to prepare our heart? What do we do each day when we

692
00:40:51,119 --> 00:40:57,299
approach the Lord? I've made this comment before, and I just observe it. I'm not singling

693
00:40:57,299 --> 00:41:04,539
out a particular region of the world, but I find it more prominent with the Asian community

694
00:41:04,539 --> 00:41:10,539
that when they go into a church, they immediately sit down and begin praying before the service

695
00:41:10,539 --> 00:41:17,339
even begins. I've seen it often. And I'm not suggesting that no other culture or people

696
00:41:17,339 --> 00:41:21,879
group do that. One thing that we started in our church was having a time of prayer before

697
00:41:21,879 --> 00:41:26,859
our services. Why? Because I want my heart to be ready. I've made known that that time

698
00:41:26,919 --> 00:41:31,159
of prayer is not to pray for the person that's sick, the person that's got this ailment or

699
00:41:31,159 --> 00:41:37,139
that ailment or this thing or that travel. No, it's God, work in my heart in this service.

700
00:41:37,139 --> 00:41:43,239
Do something, Lord. It's really the purpose of that prayer time. But break up your fallow

701
00:41:43,239 --> 00:41:54,279
ground. Because if it's hard, if it's hard, the soil's not ready, your heart's not ready

702
00:41:54,279 --> 00:42:02,659
to receive the seed, to take in that root. And the reality is that you and only you

703
00:42:02,659 --> 00:42:07,239
know the condition of your heart. And I understand, listen, the Bible says the heart is deceitful

704
00:42:07,239 --> 00:42:11,459
and desperately wicked. Who can know it? The Lord searched at the heart. He tries the rains.

705
00:42:11,459 --> 00:42:22,559
He knows. And here this evening, the soil needs preparation in order to yield a harvest.

706
00:42:22,559 --> 00:42:29,299
And your heart and my heart break up your fallow ground. Needs to be preparation, work

